title: Wayward Language
description: A language file for a Wayward mod.

extends.description: The name of the language that this file extends.

alternateFontStyle.description: Whether this language requires an alternate, non-pixelated font in order to render correctly.

dictionaries.description: An object containing all the dictionaries and their entries. For a list of all dictionaries, see: https://waywardgame.github.io/enums/dictionary.html

pluralizationRules.description: An object containing "pluralization rules" for the language. These affect how nouns in this language are pluralized. For example, you could make a rule that changed "octopus" to "octopi"

pluralRules.description: An array containing mappings from a singular noun to a plural noun.

singularRules.description: An array containing mappings from a plural noun to a singular noun.

uncountables.description: An array containing a list of nouns which have an identical plural and singular form.

irregularRules.description: An array containing a list of tuples, the first value of which represents a singular noun and the second value of which represents its plural noun.

articleRules.description: Rules for how definite and indefinite articles are added to nouns. Uses counts and regular expressions to match nouns to their respective articles.

indefinite.description: An array containing a list of tuples, the first value of which is a number representing how many of an item must be present for the rule to match (null to match all), the second value of which is a regular expression matching a part/parts of a noun, and the third value of which is a replacement for matches of that regular expression.

definite.description: An array containing a list of tuples, the first value of which is a number representing how many of an item must be present for the rule to match (null to match all), the second value of which is a regular expression matching a part/parts of a noun, and the third value of which is a replacement for matches of that regular expression.

contextRules.description: Rules for how Wayward's language system understands text. This is used, for example, for determining which characters should be capitalised in a title.

isWord.description: A regular expression matching a word character. In english, this is just /\w/

isWordSeparator.description: A regular expression matching a word separator. In english, this is just /[\s-\/]/ (matching whitespace, dashes, and slashes.)

isSentenceSeparator.description: A regular expression matching a sentence separator. In english, this is just /[.!?\n:]/ (matching periods, exclamation points, question marks, newlines, and colons.

shouldCapitalizeWord.description: A regular expression matching the start of any word that should be capitalised. In english, this is instead a list of words that *shouldn't* be capitalised, for example /(?!a\b)(?!an\b)(?!the\b)(?!and\b)/
